{
  "texts": [
    "The DNN model achieved a 67% precision and a 67.2% accuracy throughout the test set.",
    "Two Deep Neural Network (DNN) models were developed in Lee et al (2021) to identify and assist low-performing students.",
    "Based on student's learning behaviors, the first model effectively assessed student performance.",
    "The second model, on the other hand, effectively predicted student performance based on how they responded to the exercise questions.",
    "The dataset for the study was gathered from two MOOC courses offered by National Tsing Hua University."
  ]
}